  "text": "To implement NTCQ with an 8PSK constellation, we use Ungerboeck's rate 2/3 convolutional code [CITATION_1] as in Fig. 1 . In the figure, the smaller the index the less significant the bit, e.g., b in,1 and b in,2 are the least and the most significant input bit, respectively. The trellis with output sequences in decimal digits from the convolutional code is shown in Fig. 2 , and the 8PSK constellation is depicted in Fig. 3 .",
